Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with graded porous cathode were fabricated via a multilayer tape casting and co-firing technique, which is a low-cost and reproducible fabrication process.
Titulo: Graded porous solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by multilayer tape casting and co-firing progress

Sentencas: The effects of pore formers,on the electrochemical performance of graded cathode are studied to minimize cathodic polarization resistance.
Titulo: Graded porous solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by multilayer tape casting and co-firing progress

Sentencas: Examination of the microstructures reveals that the multilayer single cell had no delamination, observable cracks, or other large defects.
Titulo: Graded porous solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by multilayer tape casting and co-firing progress

Sentencas: The cell prepared by the co-firing process exhibits low interfacial polarization resistance and high power density at the operating temperature range of 700 -800 degrees C.
Titulo: Graded porous solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by multilayer tape casting and co-firing progress

Sentencas: This simple fabrication technique can be used for optimization of electrode microstructures and cost-effective fabrication of high-performance SOFCs.
Titulo: Graded porous solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by multilayer tape casting and co-firing progress
